<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="Liset" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">XS1009</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">XS1009</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">XS1009</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Unrecognized escape sequence</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">An unexpected character follows a backslash (\) in a string. The compiler expects one of the valid escape characters. For more information, see Character Escapes.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following sample generates XS1009.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">X#</text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// XS1009-a.prg  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">class MyClass  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">{  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   static void Main()  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   {  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // The following line causes XS1009.  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      string a = &quot;\m&quot;;     </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // Try the following line instead.  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // string a = &quot;\t&quot;;  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   }  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">} </text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">A common cause of this error is using the backslash character in a file name, as the following example shows.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">X#</text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">string filename = &quot;c:\myFolder\myFile.txt&quot;;  </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">To resolve this error, use &quot;\\&quot; or the @-quoted string literal, as the following example shows.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">X#</text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// XS1009-b.prg  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">class MyClass  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">{  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   static void Main()  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   {  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // The following line causes XS1009.  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      string filename = &quot;c:\myFolder\myFile.txt&quot;;     </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // Try one of the following lines instead.  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // string filename = &quot;c:\\myFolder\\myFile.txt&quot;;  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // string filename = @&quot;c:\myFolder\myFile.txt&quot;;  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   }  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">}  </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
